article.headline: Marshall 54, East Carolina 51
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Markel Humphrey scored a game-high 12 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Mark Dorris hit a jumper with 28 seconds left to lift Marshall over East Carolina 54-51 on Wednesday night. Dorris added 11 points for Marshall (11-16, 6-7 Conference USA), which handed the Pirates their record-setting 13th consecutive loss. John Fields led East Carolina (5-21, 0-13 CUSA) with 11 points and 13 rebounds, recording his third double-double of the season. Darrell Jenkins added 10 points. East Carolina (5-21, 0-13 CUSA) was down by eight before going on a 15-2 run to take a 23-20 lead with 4:32 left before the break. The Pirates led 31-27 at halftime. There were three lead changes and five ties in the second half before Marshall pulled ahead by five points, 49-44, with 5:23 left. A dunk and pair of free throws by Fields followed by a layup by Jenkins put East Carolina up 50-49 with 4:11 left. Marshall answered with a layup from Chris Ross, but Jenkins hit a free throw to tie the game with 1:24 remaining. The Pirates called a time-out after Dorris hit his jumper. Jenkins attempted a layup but the ball rolled of the rim, and Marshall secured the rebound. Ross converted a free throw for the final margin.
